What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: 219 is a continuation of 219 with harder and more harmonically complex examples. Take it! Sarita is ok, but she is definitely overrated as a teacher (probably because she is VERY nice and everyone loves her) so definitely shop both sections.
Great course, highly recommended for absolutely all music majors or serious performers/composers/arrangers.
I would definitely recommend this course. It was very fun and you learn how to listen.
It's a fun class with a very light workload (keyboard lab can be a little daunting or little to no work at all depending on your experience). Take it with Sarita! She's awesome.

A good way to work on your skills for sightreading and analysis - take it if you've taken 218 and are interested in it. But only take it with Sarita - other instructors (I've heard) tend to be not so great/helpful.
Great course, be prepared for MUCH more challenging material than 218, in general.
Very necessary for the major or anyone who wants to improve their ear. Take it with Sarita!!
